title: melanoma cell A375, microRNA biological rep 1
treatment_protocol_ch1: Cells were trypsinized and harvested for RNA isolation. Exosomes were purified from cell culture supernatants by a combination of ultrafiltration and ultracentrifugation.
growth_protocol_ch1: normal melanocytes HEMa-LP cells were cultured in Medium 254 supplemented with Human Melanocyte Growth Supplement-2 (HMGS-2) in a 5% CO2 incubator at 37C. Malignant melanoma A375 cells were maintained in Dulbecco’s Modified Eagle Medium (DMEM) supplemented with 10% exosome-depleted fetal bovine serum (FBS). FBS was depleted of exosomes by ultracentrifugation at 100,000 x g for 16h at 4C.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA from cells and exosomes were isolated using mirVana total RNA isolation kit according to the manufacturer’s guidelines.
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated miRNA were prepared according to the standard protocol for Genisphere FlashTag kit from 500 ng total RNA.
hyb_protocol: Labeled miRNA was hybridized for 16 hr at 45C on Affymetrix miRNA 1.0. GeneChips were washed and stained in the Affymetrix Fluidics Station 450 using Fluidics Protocol FS450-0003.
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using Affymetrix' GeneChip Scanner GCS3000 7G and Command Console Version 1.0
description: miRNA expression data from A375 cells.
data_processing: The data were analyzed with Partek Genomics Suite 6.5 using RMA default analysis settings as normalization method and a 2-Way ANOVA was set-up to determine differentially expressed miRNAs.
